1 47-18-04. When homestead subject to execution.
2 A homestead is subject to execution or forced sale in satisfaction of judgments obtained in
3 the following cases:
4 1. On debts secured by mechanics', construction, or laborers' liens for work or labor done
5 or performed or material furnished exclusively for the improvement of the same.
6 2. On debts secured by mortgage on the premises executed and acknowledged by both
7 husband and wife, or an unmarried claimant.
8 3. On debts created for the purchase thereof and for all taxes accruing and levied
9 thereonof the homestead.
10 4. On all other debts, excluding property taxes and special assessments accruing and
11 levied on the homestead, when, upon an appraisal as provided by section 47-18-06, it
12 appears that the value of the homestead is more than one hundred fifty thousand
13 dollars over and above liens or encumbrances on the homestead, and then only to the
14 extent of any value in excess of the sum total of the liens and encumbrances plus said
15 one hundred fifty thousand dollars.
16 SECTION 3. AMENDMENT. Section 47-18-18 of the North Dakota Century Code is
17 amended and reenacted as follows:
18 47-18-18. Declaration of homestead - How executed and acknowledged.
19 1. In order to select a homestead the:
20 a. The claimant shall execute and acknowledge, in the same manner as a grant of
21 real property is acknowledged, a declaration of homestead, and file the
22 declaration for record.
23 b. A claim of a homestead by a debtor who received a discharge is a declaration of
24 homestead.
25 c. Filing for record in the recorder's office of the county where the homestead is
26 located a certified copy with the legal description of the discharge constitutes
27 notice that the property is a homestead and exempt from judgments.
28 2. A declaration executed under this section is executed under penalty of perjury.
