1 57-28-03. Contents of notice of tax lien.
2 Notice of foreclosure of tax lien must include:
3 1. The description of the property.
4 2. The amount of delinquent property taxes and special assessments, with penalties,
5 interest, and foreclosure costs, for the tax year foreclosed.
6 3. The total amount required to satisfy the property tax lien.
7 4. The time when the foreclosure will occur.
8 5. Information related to the homestead exemption in chapter 47 - 18, including the
9 process to claim a property as a homestead.
10 SECTION 5. A new section to chapter 57-28 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
11 and enacted as follows:
12 Lien priority.
13 A lien for unpaid property taxes or special assessments under this chapter has priority over
14 any judgment, mortgage, or other lien or claim entered against the real property except for liens
15 under section 35-34-02.1. A lien for property taxes has priority over a lien for special
16 assessments.
